The paper deals with the problem of computing a low-rank factorization of a matrix in the streaming model, which is a common topic in the areas of data structures (cs.DS), information theory (cs.IT), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the problem in the context of differential privacy, which is a topic in both data management (cs.DB) and theoretical computer science (cs.DM).
